Only eat at FIX-U-PLATE if you don't love yourself!

I go to this place all the time... ever since I took the chance and made the choice to go in and  try the food I never stopped going... but after my experience with the cashier today I felt it necessary to give this review.  I had 3 of the small styrofoam containers one had a meal for my husband with consisted of spinach rice, stewed peas 2 pieces of stew pork and 2 pieces of oxtail and some kale salad over it all... I put oxtail GRAVY in the other 2 containers(no oxtail).  As I go to cash my purchase the young lady places the 1st container (with the oxtail) separately on the scale entered a cost into the register and then attempted to weigh the other 2 containers... when I asked her what she was doing she said she saw me take more than 5 pieces of oxtail... I didn't even take 5 pieces of a variation of meats let alone 5 pieces of oxtail... this is sheer distrust of the customers that is keeping you in business... I am absolutely horrified and utterly embarrassed at the treatment I received today.  What I should have done was leave the food right there and walked out, let them deconstruct and see how much pieces of oxtail was in there.  I asked for the manager and was told the manager wasn't there, I asked for the name of the manager and she refused to give me the name, she told me they do not give names out🙄.  Like really??!! Just goes to show the lack of professionalism and customer service at this establishment.  I need to speak to management and will not stop until I get a hold of someone!!  If you decide to go to this restaurant call someone to watch you take the oxtail out... bring it to their attention because they will rob you over a piece of oxtail if you hover over it too long... they charge $8.99 a lb vs $6.99 a lb if they suspect you took more than the allotted 5 pieces .  #theoxtailnazi
